      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, im seeing some weirdness in our ec2 instances. getting \"Connection reset by peer\" errors in the logs every few hours but it's totally intermittent. here is a snippet of the cloudwatch log:\n\n2023-10-24T14:22:01Z i-0a1234567890abcdef error: connection reset by peer (errno 104)\n2023-10-24T14:25:12Z i-0a1234567890abcdef error: connection reset by peer (errno 104)\n\nany idea if this could be a security group or NACL thing? or should i look at the app layer?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
