    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the app logs dont show much before the reset happens, its like they just vanish. could it be an idle timeout on the load balancer or some kind of networking glitch? also curious if it could be something at the OS level, like the kernel just dropping the connection for no reason.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An idle timeout on your load balancer is a very strong possibility, as it would cleanly terminate inactive connections without application logging. You should also inspect the system logs (`journalctl` or `/var/log/messages`) on the EC2 instance itself for kernel-level TCP/IP socket errors or resource exhaustion messages. If the problem persists, suspecting an intermediary firewall or NAT gateway behavior becomes the next logical troubleshooting step.",
      "source": "target",
