    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk, it just feels so random. like one minute everything is fine and the next it's just cutting out. it's almost like there's some invisible thing messing with the packets or something. is there any way to actually see if a packet is being intentionally dropped by a middlebox vs just timing out?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To distinguish between a timeout and an active packet drop by a middlebox, capturing network traffic is necessary. You can use tools like `tcpdump` directly on the EC2 instance, filtering for the affected traffic, to observe whether the FIN/RST packet is received or if the connection simply stalls. If you see no packets leaving or returning around the failure time, an external device is likely dropping them.",
      "source": "target",
